      "message": "put runFunc at the end, then declare it inline with the call, e.g.\n\n  return runExclusive(lockFilePath, drainFilePath, timeout, pollingInterval, func() error {\n    return runCommand(command)\n  })\n\nI would also strongly consider making a lockOptions struct:\n\n  type lockOptions struct {\n    lockFilePath string\n    drainFilePath string\n    timeout time.Time\n    pollingInterval time.Duration\n  }\n\nAdditionally, I would reconsider having all of these things be part of the public API; mmutex is supposed to implement a protocol where all of these are defined as part of the protocol (i.e. they\u0027re derived from env.\n\nAdditionally additionally, I would remove `timeout` here, and instead pass a context.Context and use it\u0027s built-in cancellation functionality. Go\u0027s stdlib also has support for context.Context cancellation of subprocesses, which is the recommended way to do that.",
